>Description:
Consider this example:

(let ([x 1]
      [y 2]
      [z 3])
  (foo x y z))

Now uncomment [y 2] and reindent;

(let ([x 1]
      #;[y 2]
        [z 3])
  (foo x y z))

The [z 3] is now off by 2. Presumably adding a -2 to
the indentation following a line ending in a #; comment
will do the trick.
